DataElement.preferredName: Animal Biological Entity Birth Country Code ISO21090.CD.v1.0
DataElement.preferredDefinition: A non-human living organism that has membranous cell walls, requires oxygen and organic foods, and is capable of voluntary movement, as distinguished from a plant or mineral. EXAMPLE(S): dog, cat, mouse A coded value specifying the name of the country in which the biologic entity is born.
